            <Title>Chapter 3 - The Vagrant Fucker</Title>
            <Synopsis>Things happen to move the story forward.  </Synopsis>
            <Text>Mr. Plutoro was not pleased. He’s on my phone right now living up to his very special name “Angry Yelling Man”. He’s angry and yelling.

“Those files are supposed to be backed up every mother fucking night!”

“Yes they are Mr. Plutoro.”

“SO WHY CAN’T YOU GET ME MY FILE!”

“I’ve already done so and sent the recovered file to you Mr. Plutoro.” In my best Dolly Pardon voice.

“THIS IS NOT MY FILE!”

“sales underscore takeout dot x-l-s, correct Mr. Plutoro?”

A loud sigh from the ass end of the phone call.

“I’ve already done so and sent you the recovered file, Mr. Plutoro.”

“No! WHERE IS THE MOTHER FUCKING CHANGES I MADE MOTHER FUCKING THIS MORNING!?”

“You made mother what?” Honestly confused for a moment, recovered and spent the next 37 minutes explaining how time works. Mr. Plutoro was so moved by the metaphor of the beautifully lilting flower that he sent me a bouquet of flowers with an apology the next day.

Just kidding, he kept yelling.

“Polly, were you planning on borking with Cal this weekend?”

“What.”

“Uhm…can I stay over this weekend? I need some alone time.”

“You live by yourself?”

“Yes.”

“You want to hang out this weekend?” Polly knows before she answered. Her and Cal don’t mind the company, especially now that Mel has gone and gotten herself killed. Speaking of which, that is exactly why I want to go over there. It’s been keeping me up at night. Polly gives me the OK, time for a weekend of listening about cars and talking about my obsession. Yay!

“So what’s this dude’s name?”

“Rustles Ruskotina”

“Stop fucking with me.”

“Rustles Ruskovitz, Ruskovitz, right honey”

Polly gives Cal a cute smile and smacks him with her novel. “Call me honey again darling sweetypoofs, and I’ll use the dictionary next time.”

“Muhahahahahaha” I maniacally laugh.

“You’re brother is a dork. One hundred and fifty percent.”

“Yes I know cutie-poop.”

Clearing my throat I intervene “So this guy…was working for Mel?”

“Nope, but he got involved somehow. Saw it on his noir blog.”

“What.”

“He’s my cousin dude, I read his blogs.”

“This guy has multiple blogs?”

“Polly have you met Rustles.”

“Yes, I didn’t like it.”

“How’s that?”

“I felt like he was a black hole, sucking the feeling out of me. His pasty skin looked sticky to the touch, inviting my tongue to it. I wanted to lick his damn face. The dame, he said, was in some kind of trouble.”

“Why are you talking like some shitty noir film?”

Polly ducks her head into her tea and shrugs, slurping, obviously not wanting to answer&quot;

“Why are you talking like some shitty noir film?”

“Dude, you know she’s got a black-belt right?” Cal snorts and nearly ducks away quick enough to avoid the flying literature.

“I love how she threw the novel at you instead of” SMACK “dammit! why does you have two dictionaries??”

“Obviously so I have a spare to read. The only thing I’m holding now is this hard baked mug…”

“So yeah, Cal, boyfriend of my beautiful lovely smart sister. Teehee. Can you give me Rusko’s number?”
</Text>
