            <Title>Chapter 4 - Lessons in Noir</Title>
            <Synopsis>Sam meets the wannabe's and maybe regrets it.
</Synopsis>
            <Text>“So the donuts, why does every class start with me eating donuts?”

Sam waddled back over to his desk, slumping on the squeaky chair.

“To eat donuts, this sugary pastry…” Sam holds up a frosted donut, sugar all over his ﬁngers “…is to understand proper criminal investigation. The donut hole is the window to the criminals heart.”

“What.” Hank says quietly, mostly to himself.

“I SAID DONUTS ARE THE WINDOW TO THE CRIMINAL HEART. The pain you feel in your tummy when you have a dozen of these god deserts is the growth of our soul. It’s expanding, allowing insights beyond your imagination.”

I’d been at this for three days now. I’m pretty certain Sam is crazy but I am getting free donuts.

“Uhm, about that Hank. I need a $20 to cover the cost of these donuts.”

“What.” Surprised at Sam’s ability to read his mind.

“You were narrating your thoughts. People tend to do that around me for some reason.”

“I was not…oh my god I was.”

“Also, I’m not crazy. Just full of sugary love.”

“…”

“Also, saying dot dot dot doesn’t actually work.”

I’m pretty sure he’s crazy and I’m also crazy.
</Text>
